The above exercise shows that $P_m (FF)$ is finite-dimensional. The broader set $P(FF)$, however, is *infinite-dimensional*. In fact, $P(FF)$ is generated by the infinite basis

$
  P(FF) = gen(1\, x\, x^2\, ...,).
$
